### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### 1. Register User 1
POST http://localhost:3000/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "display_name": "Alice Wonderland"
}

### Register User 2
POST http://localhost:3000/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "display_name": "Bob Builder"
}

### Register User 3
POST http://localhost:3000/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "charlie",
  "display_name": "Charlie Chaplin"
}

### Test 409 Conflict (User already exists)
POST http://localhost:3000/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "display_name": "Alice Clone"
}

### 2. Get User
GET http://localhost:3000/users/alice

### 3. Send Friend Request (Alice -> Bob)
POST http://localhost:3000/friend-request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "alice",
  "to": "bob"
}

### Send Friend Request (Bob -> Charlie)
POST http://localhost:3000/friend-request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "bob",
  "to": "charlie"
}

### 4. Accept Friend Request (Bob validates Alice's request)
POST http://localhost:3000/friend-accept
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "alice",
  "to": "bob"
}

### Accept Friend Request (Charlie validates Bob's request)
POST http://localhost:3000/friend-accept
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "bob",
  "to": "charlie"
}

### 5. Get Friends (Alice's direct friends)
GET http://localhost:3000/users/alice/friends

### 6. Create Post (Alice - public)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "content": "Hello world from Alice! This is public.",
  "visibility": "public"
}

### Create Post (Bob - friends)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "content": "Bob is talking to his direct friends.",
  "visibility": "friends"
}

### Create Post (Bob - friends of friends)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "content": "Bob spans 2 hops! FOF can see this.",
  "visibility": "friends_of_friends"
}

### Create Post (Charlie - private)
POST http://localhost:3000/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "charlie",
  "content": "A secret post that only Charlie will see.",
  "visibility": "private"
}

### 7. Get Alice's Feed 
# (Should see her own, Bob's public/friends/FOF, but not Charlie's private)
GET http://localhost:3000/feed/alice

### Get Charlie's Feed 
# (Charlie is a FOF of Alice. So he shouldn't see bob's "friends" post, but will see bob's "FOF" post)
GET http://localhost:3000/feed/charlie

### 8. Get Friends of Friends (Alice FOF should be Charlie)
GET http://localhost:3000/users/alice/friends-of-friends

### 9. Get Mutual Friends (between Alice and Charlie should be Bob)
GET http://localhost:3000/users/alice/mutual-friends/charlie

### 10. Suggestions for Alice
GET http://localhost:3000/users/alice/suggestions

### 11. Send Message (Alice to Charlie -> Success, since they are FOF)
POST http://localhost:3000/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "alice",
  "to": "charlie",
  "content": "Hi Charlie, I am Bob's friend!"
}

### Register a complete stranger (Dave)
POST http://localhost:3000/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "dave",
  "display_name": "Dave Stranger"
}

### Test 403 Forbidden Messenger Auth (Alice to Dave -> Fails because distance > 2)
POST http://localhost:3000/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "alice",
  "to": "dave",
  "content": "Hi Dave! Spam message."
}

### 12. Get messages for Charlie
GET http://localhost:3000/messages/charlie
